---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Calm Walks Workshop: Hands-On Coaching for Reactive Dogs | July 22 | Down 4 Paws"
  description="A 90-minute hands-on workshop in Norwood, MA on Wednesday, July 22. Practice the Down 4 Paws Method with your own dog while Pam Brown coaches you through every step. Limited to 10 working teams. $99 early registration."
>
  <!-- HEADER -->
  <header class="fixed top-0 left-0 right-0 z-50 bg-white shadow-sm">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-8 py-4 flex items-center justify-between">
      <a href="https://down4paws.com" class="relative z-10">
        <img src="/images/d4p-logo.png" alt="Down 4 Paws Dog Training" class="h-9 md:h-11" />
      </a>
      <a
        href="#register"
        class="relative z-10 font-display text-sm md:text-base bg-orange text-white px-5 py-2 rounded-full hover:bg-orange-bright transition-all duration-200 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-orange/20 hover:-translate-y-px"
      >
        Reserve My Spot
      </a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="relative bg-cream overflow-hidden pt-20 pb-0 md:pt-0">
    <div class="absolute top-12 right-[8%] w-64 h-64 bg-purple-soft/40 rounded-full blur-3xl"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-40 left-[5%] w-48 h-48 bg-orange-soft/30 rounded-full blur-2xl"></div>

    <div class="relative max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-8 w-full">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-6 items-center md:min-h-[60svh] md:py-32 pt-4 pb-10">

        <div class="md:col-span-7 space-y-6">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2.5 bg-orange/8 border border-orange/12 rounded-full px-4 py-1.5">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-orange rounded-full animate-pulse"></span>
            <span class="text-orange text-xs font-bold tracking-widest uppercase">Hands-On Workshop &middot; 10 Teams Max</span>
          </div>

          <h1>
            <span class="block font-display text-charcoal text-[clamp(2rem,5.5vw,3.8rem)] leading-[1.1] mb-2">
              The Advice Makes Sense at Home.
            </span>
            <span class="block font-display text-charcoal text-[clamp(2rem,5.5vw,3.8rem)] leading-[1.1] mb-2">
              Then Another Dog Shows Up,
            </span>
            <span class="block font-display text-orange text-[clamp(2rem,5.5vw,3.8rem)] leading-[1.1]">
              And It All Falls Apart.
            </span>
          </h1>

          <p class="text-warm-gray text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-lg">
            A 90-minute working workshop where you and your dog practice calm walks together, outside, with Pam coaching you through every rep. You'll learn to read your dog, catch stress early, and handle real moments while they're actually happening.
          </p>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 items-center">
            <a
              href="#register"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 font-display bg-purple text-white text-lg px-7 py-3.5 rounded-full hover:bg-purple-deep transition-all duration-200 hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-purple/20 hover:-translate-y-px group"
            >
              Reserve My Spot
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" /></svg>
            </a>
            <span class="inline-flex flex-col px-2 py-1">
              <span class="font-display text-purple text-lg leading-tight">$99 early registration</span>
              <span class="text-warm-gray text-xs">$119 after Saturday, July 18</span>
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Workshop details card -->
        <div class="md:col-span-5">
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-orange/5 rounded-3xl translate-x-3 translate-y-3"></div>
            <div class="relative bg-white rounded-3xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-beige">
              <p class="font-display text-purple text-xl mb-5">Workshop Details</p>
              <div class="space-y-4 mb-5">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                  <div class="w-9 h-9 bg-purple-mist rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                    <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-purple" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 7V3m8 4V3m-9 8h10M5 21h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2z" /></svg>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <p class="text-charcoal font-semibold text-sm">Wednesday, July 22</p>
                    <p class="text-warm-gray text-xs">6:30 PM - 8:00 PM</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                  <div class="w-9 h-9 bg-orange-soft rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                    <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-orange" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17.657 16.657L13.414 20.9a1.998 1.998 0 01-2.827 0l-4.244-4.243a8 8 0 1111.314 0z" /><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 11a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" /></svg>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <p class="text-charcoal font-semibold text-sm">In Person, Norwood Area</p>
                    <p class="text-warm-gray text-xs">Exact location sent after registration</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                  <div class="w-9 h-9 bg-sage/20 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                    <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-sage" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" /></svg>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <p class="text-charcoal font-semibold text-sm">Limited to 10 Working Teams</p>
                    <p class="text-warm-gray text-xs">Individual coaching for every team</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="h-px bg-beige mb-5"></div>

              <!-- Pricing -->
              <div class="space-y-2">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline">
                  <p class="text-charcoal font-semibold text-sm">Early registration</p>
                  <p class="font-display text-purple text-lg">$99</p>
                </div>
                <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline">
                  <p class="text-warm-gray text-xs">After Saturday, July 18</p>
                  <p class="text-warm-gray font-semibold text-sm">$119</p>
                </div>
                <p class="text-warm-gray text-xs pt-2">Each registration covers one dog and up to two people from the same household.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Full-width hero image -->
    <div class="relative max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-8 pb-12">
      <div class="relative rounded-3xl overflow-hidden shadow-xl shadow-charcoal/10">
        <img
          src="/images/hero-in-person.jpg"
          alt="A woman walking her dog calmly on a loose leash down a quiet, tree-lined street"
          class="w-full h-auto object-cover"
          loading="eager"
        />
        <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-end">
          <div class="w-full p-4 md:p-6">
            <span class="bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm text-charcoal font-display text-sm md:text-base px-4 py-2 rounded-full shadow-sm">
              Not a lecture. You and your dog do the work, with Pam beside you.
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PAIN OF SUCCESS -->
  <section class="relative bg-charcoal py-20 md:py-28 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03]" style="background-image: url('data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg width=&quot;60&quot; height=&quot;60&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 60 60&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;%3E%3Cg fill=&quot;none&quot; fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot;%3E%3Cg fill=&quot;%23ffffff&quot; fill-opacity=&quot;1&quot;%3E%3Cpath d=&quot;M36 34v-4h-2v4h-4v2h4v4h2v-4h4v-2h-4zm0-30V0h-2v4h-4v2h4v4h2V6h4V4h-4zM6 34v-4H4v4H0v2h4v4h2v-4h4v-2H6zM6 4V0H4v4H0v2h4v4h2V6h4V4H6z&quot;/%3E%3C/g%3E%3C/g%3E%3C/svg%3E');"></div>

    <div class="relative max-w-5xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-8">
      <p class="font-display text-orange text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-8">You've Been Doing the Work</p>

      <div class="space-y-8 md:space-y-10">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:col-span-1 pt-1">
            <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full border-2 border-orange/40 flex items-center justify-center">
              <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 bg-orange rounded-full"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-11">
            <p class="text-white/90 text-xl md:text-2xl leading-relaxed font-light">
              You've watched the videos. Maybe you joined the free workshop. You understand thresholds and triggers now. <span class="text-orange font-medium">Understanding was supposed to be the hard part.</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:col-span-1 pt-1">
            <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full border-2 border-orange/40 flex items-center justify-center">
              <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 bg-orange rounded-full"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-11">
            <p class="text-white/90 text-xl md:text-2xl leading-relaxed font-light">
              Then a dog rounds the corner and your brain empties out. Treats in the wrong hand. Leash tight. <span class="text-orange font-medium">Every plan you had is gone in half a second.</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:col-span-1 pt-1">
            <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full border-2 border-orange/40 flex items-center justify-center">
              <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 bg-orange rounded-full"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-11">
            <p class="text-white/90 text-xl md:text-2xl leading-relaxed font-light">
              You replay it on the way home. "I should have turned earlier. I should have stayed calm." <span class="text-orange font-medium">You knew what to do. You just couldn't do it in the moment.</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-14 md:mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-white/10">
        <p class="font-display text-white text-2xl md:text-3xl max-w-2xl">
          That's not a knowledge problem. That's a practice problem.<br/>
          <span class="text-orange">And practice is exactly what this workshop is.</span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE METHOD / WHERE THIS FITS -->
  <section class="bg-white py-20 md:py-28 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-8">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10 md:gap-16 items-start">
        <div class="md:col-span-6">
          <p class="font-display text-orange text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">The Down 4 Paws Method</p>
          <h2 class="font-display text-charcoal text-3xl md:text-4xl leading-tight mb-6">
            Understanding your dog was step one. This is step three.
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-warm-gray leading-relaxed text-lg">
            <p>
              Every family I work with moves through the same four stages. The free online workshop covered the first one, what I call Behavior Translation: why your dog reacts and what they're feeling when it happens.
            </p>
            <p>
              This workshop is where it becomes real. Your hands on the leash, your dog at your side, and me right there coaching your timing, your spacing, and your decisions.
            </p>
            <p class="text-charcoal font-medium">
              Haven't seen the free online workshop yet? Register anyway and I'll send you the replay, so you arrive ready.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-8 bg-cream rounded-2xl p-6 border border-beige">
            <p class="font-display text-orange text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">Behavior Translation&trade;</p>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div>
                <p class="text-warm-gray text-xs uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold mb-1">You see</p>
                <p class="text-charcoal font-medium leading-relaxed">"My dog stopped listening."</p>
              </div>
              <div class="h-px bg-beige"></div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-orange text-xs uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold mb-1">Your dog is experiencing</p>
                <p class="text-charcoal font-medium leading-relaxed">"The environment suddenly became more valuable than staying connected."</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-warm-gray text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">That shift, from correcting behavior to understanding it, changes the whole conversation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-6">
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-5 border border-beige">
              <p class="font-display text-purple text-lg mb-1">1. Understand</p>
              <p class="text-warm-gray text-sm leading-relaxed">Learn why the behavior happens and what your dog is experiencing. Understanding creates clarity. Everything else builds on it.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-5 border border-beige">
              <p class="font-display text-purple text-lg mb-1">2. Structure</p>
              <p class="text-warm-gray text-sm leading-relaxed">Build routines and predictability that lower stress for your dog and your family.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-purple rounded-2xl p-5 shadow-lg shadow-purple/20 relative">
              <span class="absolute top-4 right-5 bg-orange text-white text-[10px] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase px-3 py-1 rounded-full">This workshop</span>
              <p class="font-display text-white text-lg mb-1">3. Practice</p>
              <p class="text-white/80 text-sm leading-relaxed">Apply the skills where life actually happens, with coaching in the moment. Progress over perfection.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-5 border border-beige">
              <p class="font-display text-purple text-lg mb-1">4. Support</p>
              <p class="text-warm-gray text-sm leading-relaxed">Keep building confidence through adolescence, changes, and every new stage of life.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY DOWN 4 PAWS -->
  <section class="bg-purple py-16 md:py-20 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-8">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-12 items-center">
        <div class="md:col-span-5">
          <p class="font-display text-orange-soft text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">Why Families Choose Down 4 Paws</p>
          <h2 class="font-display text-white text-3xl md:text-4xl leading-tight">
            We don't start with obedience. We start with calm.
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-7 space-y-4 text-white/80 leading-relaxed text-lg">
          <p>
            Most dog training focuses on controlling behavior. We focus on understanding it first. Instead of asking "How do I stop this?", we ask "Why does this behavior make sense to my dog?" Once behavior makes sense, training gets much easier.
          </p>
          <p class="text-white font-medium">
            And before any of it, we help your dog become calm enough to learn. A calm brain learns better than an overwhelmed one.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT YOU'LL PRACTICE -->
  <section class="bg-cream py-20 md:py-28 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-xl mb-14">
        <p class="font-display text-orange text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">90 Minutes, Hands-On</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-charcoal text-3xl md:text-4xl leading-tight">
          What You'll Practice Together
        </h2>
        <p class="text-warm-gray mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          This is a coaching workshop, not a lecture. Throughout the 90 minutes, I'll coach your leash handling, your timing, your reward placement, how you read your dog's body language, and the decisions you make in the moment. Here's how it runs.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="relative">
        <div class="absolute left-[18px] md:left-[22px] top-0 bottom-0 w-px bg-gradient-to-b from-purple/20 via-purple/10 to-transparent hidden md:block"></div>

        <div class="space-y-6 md:space-y-8">
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-4 md:gap-6 items-start">
            <div class="md:col-span-1 flex items-start">
              <div class="relative z-10 w-10 h-10 md:w-11 md:h-11 bg-purple rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center shadow-md shadow-purple/15">
                <span class="font-display text-white text-base">1</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-11 bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-7 border border-beige hover:border-purple-soft/60 transition-colors group">
              <h3 class="font-display text-purple text-xl mb-2 group-hover:text-purple-deep transition-colors">Calm Before Commands</h3>
              <p class="text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
                Before anyone takes a step, you'll practice Behavior Translation: reading your dog's emotional state (and checking your own). Then you'll set up your leash and rewards properly, and use sniffing resets and treat scatters to find your dog's personal reset button. Preparation creates success.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-4 md:gap-6 items-start">
            <div class="md:col-span-1 flex items-start">
              <div class="relative z-10 w-10 h-10 md:w-11 md:h-11 bg-purple rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center shadow-md shadow-purple/15">
                <span class="font-display text-white text-base">2</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-11 bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-7 border border-beige hover:border-purple-soft/60 transition-colors group">
              <h3 class="font-display text-purple text-xl mb-2 group-hover:text-purple-deep transition-colors">Engagement Before Movement</h3>
              <p class="text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
                The Name Game, check-ins, eye contact, and engagement work. The goal: your dog starts voluntarily checking in with you before the walk even begins. You'll practice your reinforcement timing until it clicks.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-4 md:gap-6 items-start">
            <div class="md:col-span-1 flex items-start">
              <div class="relative z-10 w-10 h-10 md:w-11 md:h-11 bg-purple rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center shadow-md shadow-purple/15">
                <span class="font-display text-white text-base">3</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-11 bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-7 border border-beige hover:border-purple-soft/60 transition-colors group">
              <h3 class="font-display text-purple text-xl mb-2 group-hover:text-purple-deep transition-colors">Calm Walking Skills</h3>
              <p class="text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
                Starting calmly, pacing, loose leash handling, stopping, changing direction, emergency U-turns, and walking away from pressure. The moves you'll actually use, drilled until they're in your hands and not just your head.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-4 md:gap-6 items-start">
            <div class="md:col-span-1 flex items-start">
              <div class="relative z-10 w-10 h-10 md:w-11 md:h-11 bg-orange rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center shadow-md shadow-orange/15">
                <span class="font-display text-white text-base">4</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-11 bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-7 border border-beige hover:border-orange-soft/60 transition-colors group">
              <h3 class="font-display text-orange text-xl mb-2 group-hover:text-orange-bright transition-colors">Recovery Practice</h3>
              <p class="text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
                The heart of the workshop. Your dog notices a trigger, you stay calm, create space, re-engage, and your dog recovers. You'll run that sequence in a controlled setting with coaching in real time. We celebrate recovery, not perfection.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-4 md:gap-6 items-start">
            <div class="md:col-span-1 flex items-start">
              <div class="relative z-10 w-10 h-10 md:w-11 md:h-11 bg-purple rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center shadow-md shadow-purple/15">
                <span class="font-display text-white text-base">5</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-11 bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-7 border border-beige hover:border-purple-soft/60 transition-colors group">
              <h3 class="font-display text-purple text-xl mb-2 group-hover:text-purple-deep transition-colors">Your Individual Success Plan</h3>
              <p class="text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
                Every team leaves with one strength to keep building, one priority to focus on, one homework assignment, and one specific recommendation for your very next walk. Not generic advice. Yours.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RECOVERY -->
  <section class="bg-purple-deep py-16 md:py-24 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-display text-white text-3xl md:text-4xl leading-tight mb-4">
        Progress isn't measured by perfection.<br class="hidden md:block" /> It's measured by recovery.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-white/70 text-lg mb-10">Can your dog:</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-3 md:gap-4 mb-10">
        <div class="bg-white/10 rounded-2xl px-4 py-5">
          <p class="text-white font-medium leading-snug">Notice another dog?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/10 rounded-2xl px-4 py-5">
          <p class="text-white font-medium leading-snug">Take a breath?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/10 rounded-2xl px-4 py-5">
          <p class="text-white font-medium leading-snug">Look back at you?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/10 rounded-2xl px-4 py-5">
          <p class="text-white font-medium leading-snug">Choose to keep walking?</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="font-display text-orange-soft text-xl md:text-2xl">
        Those moments tell us your dog is learning. That's real progress.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT YOU LEAVE WITH -->
  <section class="bg-white py-20 md:py-28 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-8">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10 md:gap-16 items-start">
        <div class="md:col-span-6">
          <p class="font-display text-orange text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">Walking Out the Door</p>
          <h2 class="font-display text-charcoal text-3xl md:text-4xl leading-tight mb-6">
            What You'll Take Home
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
